items.text:
‼️Casting Call! ‼️

Wir suchen einen Darsteller oder eine Darstellerin im Alter von ca. 40–50 Jahren für einen Image- und How-to-Dreh im handwerklichen Bereich. 🔨

‼️Anforderungen:
– authentisches Auftreten
– handwerkliches Geschick (bitte keine zwei linken Hände)
– Freude am Thema DIY/Handwerk
– kleine Sprechrolle vor der Kamera
– Standort: idealerweise NRW, bevorzugt Großraum Düsseldorf

Drehtag in NRW, voraussichtlich im Dezember oder Januar/Februar.
Option auf regelmäßige Folgeprojekte.

‼️Bitte bewerbt euch mit:
– Fotos
– Gagenerwartung für 1 Drehtag
– kurzem Video, in dem ihr eine kleine handwerkliche Tätigkeit ausführt.

Kommentiere mit "Düsseldorf" um den Bewerbungslink zu erhalten! ❤️

items.text:
🎯 Make Your Self-Tapes Pop with MyAuditionAI.com

Most auditions don’t fail because of acting — they fail because casting never reaches the performance. Friction in self-tapes like poor lighting, distracting audio, or unstable framing pulls attention away before your work even lands.

MyAuditionAI.com is an advanced self-tape app and AI audition partner built to eliminate that friction. Get instant coaching and actionable feedback on lighting, sound, camera presence, and performance — all before casting ever sees your tape.

This audition preparation app includes powerful AI acting assistant features like self-tape coaching tools, a scene analysis tool for actors, script rehearsal tools, and cold read rehearsal apps to help you stay ready under pressure.

👉 Try www.MyAuditionAI.com free for 7 days and start recording auditions at home with confidence. Submit self-tapes that are clear, professional, and effortless to watch.

items.text:
Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

PS. Please note this is a university funded production and due to guidelines I am not allowed to pay anyone for their time. Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

We are getting extremely busy with back-to-back bookings, and demand is higher than ever. That means regular work, great experience, and a fun, paid role with a fast-growing party company.

💎 What we offer:

✅ Good rates of pay

**Perfect Xmas Gift for Actors! *****“THE ACTOR'S MANIFESTO: Create a Successful Acting Career”*** Amazon Books--blends techniques, neuroscience, psychology, and industry business savvy to help actors master the craft and the industry in USA.

**What it covers:**

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

The Business: Advice on navigating the entertainment industry.

Science: Neuroscience on how acting works in the brain.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

 

Written by Linda Ann Watt, SAG-AFTRA, AEA Member, SAG-AFTRA Signatory Producer/Director, MFA in Theatre Pedagogy, and 2015 Tony Award Nominee for Education. This book bridges theory and the demands of an acting career. **TheActorsManifesto.org**

items.text:
Hi everyone, I hope it’s okay to share this here.

We’ve just announced the dates for our 2026 Tucker Arts Collective Summer PROgramme in partnership with TMA Collective, and I wanted to share the information on here with you all.

This programme is built for 8-18 year olds, and designed to set young performers up for success, offering industry-standard training in singing, dancing and acting.

📅 THE DATES: 
3rd–14th August 2026
10 days, 10am–3pm - one unforgettable experience.

WHAT’S INCLUDED:
⚡️ West End masterclasses
📸 1:1 headshot session with our TMA-approved photographer
📖 Acting & speech workshops
🎙 1:1 voice studio recording session
🎶 Vocal coaching & repertoire development
🎥 1:1 acting reel filming session
🔥 Star in a professionally shot musical theatre music video
🖤 Professional mentoring from our TMA agents & creative team 

Every attendee is seen by the team across the full programme - all performers are considered for representation from Tucker Management

📍LOCATION:
Create Studios, Clarendon Park, Leicester

PRICING:
Early access: £495 until 31st March 2026
Full price: £595 from 1st April 2026
Payment plans available.

Please see our website for all the details and how to register your interest: https://www.tuckermgmt.uk/tucker-arts

Any questions, please do pop us a message, and we'd be happy to help!

Ruby

TMA founder & Senior Agent at TM Talent Agency

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‘Night Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races, ethnicities, and genders are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA “MAMA” CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie’s calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

**HORT FILM CASTING CALL – INDIGENOUS FEMALE ACTOR**

**Project Type:** Independent Short Film
**Location:** Vancouver, BC
**Shoot Dates:** March, 2026
**ROLE**
* **Indigenous / First Nations / Métis / Inuit female actor**
* **Age range:** approx. 18–25
* Acting experience preferred but not required
**CHARACTER**
* A quiet, observant young woman navigating a moment of personal change.
**REQUIREMENTS**
* Must self-identify as Indigenous
* Based in Vancouver or able to work locally
* Comfortable working on an independent short film set
**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)
* (Optional) Demo reel or self-tape

**Submit to:** hiayj23@gmail.com

Hi everyone!

I’m Arina from **DataSeeds.ai**. We produce large-scale **video & audio datasets for AI training**, and we’re currently looking for **local coordinators in different countries** to support our productions.

This is **paid work per project**, with potential for **long-term collaboration** on ongoing global briefs.

What the role includes:
– Organising filming days
– Arranging large groups of participants / extras
– Working with a simple, lean shooting setup (small crew, basic lights, clean framing)

If you’re a **film student, community organiser, photographer**, or someone who can coordinate people on camera locally — feel free to **DM me for details**!

topComments.text:
You cannot pay enough to have someone sell their voice and likeness to train AI.

Folks beware: when you help train AI on video and audio, you're literally shooting yourself in the foot. The whole point is to replace actors with AI-generated simulacrums who will work for free, won't require rest or food breaks, and won't push back against dangerous or abusive setups.
Turkeys should not vote for Christmas..

**Role Type:** Mosh Pitt BG
**Age:** 21-35
**Location:** Warehouse
**Compensation:** $100 per hour

We're looking for 8x grunge-looking guys to be part of a short-form shoot. Email or DM:

* Location
* Recent photo

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

## **🎭 Casting Breakdown: *****OUROBOROS***

A Psychological Horror film. The Fourth Film from Pineal Dreams Productions.

“When a young couple suffer the pain of a miscarriage; they retreat to a cottage in the woods to try and heal. Unfortunately they quickly discover that you can never run away from your trauma’

**DONN**

**Male | Playing age: 30-40 | Ethnicity: Open**

**Description:** Amaia’s partner. Kind, supportive, but emotionally shut down. A man attempting to cope through suppression - a misguided attempt at stoicism as he believes she must be strong to support Amaia - whose quiet unraveling becomes key to the resolution.

 **Performance notes:** Understated emotionality. Requires physical performance (injury, crawling, etc.) and strong presence in silence.

 **Comparable roles:** Michael Fassbender (*Shame*), Mads Mikkelsen (*Another Round*), Javier Bardem *(Mother!)*, Harry Dean Stanton *(Paris, Texas)*

Filming block will be the same as Amaia’s. Five-day block (Hopefully), as well as shoots at just three other locations.Ten days of filming maximum, but this could always change if re-shoots are necessary, and one day of ADR work will be required.

We know it’s frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we’ve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn’t pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That’s our promise to you.

**👥 Supporting Roles -**

**THE UMBRA**

**Male | Playing age: ANY | Tall, slender, distinctive presence | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A silent manifestation of trauma that watches over and manipulates events — a mythic observer of Amaia’s trauma. Symbol of death, memory, or fate.

 **Performance notes:** No dialogue for a vast majority of the script, though requires a sequence of some very carnival-esque dialogue. Face never seen. Must convey gravitas, mystery, and quiet threat through stillness and gaze.

 **Type:** Dancer, mime, or physical performer backgrounds welcomed. Could even opt for the possibility of a physical performer, and a separate voice-actor. So any voice-actors interested, please feel free to contact us.

Similar Roles: Doug Jones (Pan’s Labyrinth), Tim Purcell (The Babadook), Javier Botet (Slenderman)

The Umbra appears in the Cottage and scenes surrounding it, all of which will be filmed during the scheduled five-day filming block.

There will also be one additional day, in which you will be required for a single scene that takes place in a different location.

Re-shoots are of course always possible, and will be needed for one ADR session for dialogue provided during an animated sequence.

PAID - But a smaller fee than Amaia/Donn as will be required for less days.  This can be discussed upon application. We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with one scene needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require tsix days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it’s frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That’s our promise to you.

We are a very small studio, and this is our fourth short. However, our mantra has always been a ‘quality over quantity’ approach. We take great pride in not just making a film, but really thinking it through on a technical level. We appreciate classic and arthouse cinema, and are far more interested in making a good film than red carpet events.

Our three shorts so far have been screened at over 20 festivals, picking up around 14 awards - including two IMDB qualified awards. (best actor for Jackson Wright in Inside The Abyss). Our latest film has seen our lead - Tash Morley - pick up three awards. We aim for this to be our best film yet.

If interested in the roles, please contact me directly via the Pineal Dreams Instagram page. My own personal profiles - both Joshua Moulinié (Facebook/Instagram). Or Email me directly on [Moulinie23@gmail.com](mailto:Moulinie23@gmail.com)

We hope to hear from you all very soon!

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that’s been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we’ll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you’d like the free advice of some of Britain’s top lawyers (likely in region of £10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

Something to put on your Christmas List? It's not too late!

Another “actor retreat” where someone makes you pretend to be a tree?  Yeah… no thanks.

At Demand the Stage, we do actual immersive theatre training (plus cake). 

No trust falls, no potato exercises, no chanting to the moon. Just the gorgeous [The Dell House](https://www.facebook.com/thedellhouse?__cft__[0]=AZaNi0xOTTVCdEq1sbt63m_Bw0zMXP9vGnScogp_YEXlwjdbKHnjF6EQk050eBvqoLTewohDo1N2gpHgenkhF7dMUjs3eSDVEW-bDWtoWC8e2tEHDUQpWvxz5rKXRQW_qZJCD_KBM3xdH3FLW4M099yCzEpeCIvuJ__pggEWD1H5xQ6esm9JsrZlSuGE-jvmGgg&__tn__=-]K-R), practical workshops, and *all the food* you can handle.

13–15 March 2026

The Dell House, Malvern Wells

From £370pp (two nights, food included)

Limited spots. Book now on our website! Search for "Death On Demand Murder Mysteries" and click on "Demand the Stage"!

items.text:
Hi! We are LOOKING FOR A MALE ACTOR for a short film here in Budapest, set during World War II, and we aim to shoot over 2 days in late February 2026 in the Hűvösvölgy area.

The title for the film is KITARTÁS. It is a short film set during the Siege of Budapest and is a psychological exploration of the raw emotional cost in war times. The story follows Hungarian soldiers as they face a moral and physical struggle for survival in the last year of the war in Hungary. The role requires fluency in both English (for crew communication/rehearsals) and Hungarian (as the film's dialogue will be in Hungarian).

The short film will be submitted to local and international film festivals🎬

This is a low-budget short film, but it will have a symbolic payment💰

We are looking for a person to play one of the lead roles.

ÁDÁM:

Character Description: A Hungarian soldier under István’s command. Ádám is a man torn between obedience to his orders and the stirrings of his own conscience and guilt. His internal conflict becomes a major turning point in the film.

Requirements:

Male, 25–30 years old.

1.75cm - 1.80cm 

Fit or in a healthy weight

Strong presence

Must speak English and Hungarian fluently

Comfortable performing in outdoor winter conditions.

Strong dramatic ability and emotional range.

If you would like to be considered, please send your headshots, short introduction, and (if available) a showreel or acting CV to:

✉️ contactingdianag@gmail.com

Deadline: 31/12/2025

attachments.ocrText: May be a black-and-white image of the Brandenburg Gate

topComments.text: I'm a former re-enactor, I can fluently curse for 30 mins with no repeating. I know the orders of that period and the necessary drill, including firing, loading and maintanence of the M95/31 rifle. As a 45 years old, I look like a regular 25-30 years old reservist worn by war.
Tamás Kosztolnyik would be a perfect choice. Amateur actor, fitting the description perfectly, with experience in theatres and movies. I'll make sure he contacts you.

items.text:
Hi everyone!

We are running casting calls for an automotive accessories brand. Below is the casting call:

Casting for a warm and comedic commercial following a worn-down “personified car seat” who rediscovers confidence, comfort, and joy after getting a fresh start with Coverland seat covers.

Please email jieying.w@coverland.com with casting profiles, headshots and reels for audition details. 

**Production Dates:** 2-Day Production between (Jan 16-18, 2026)

**Location: **Los Angeles & Orange County, CA

**Union Status:** Non-Union

**Requesting Submissions From: **LA Locals Only

**Roles Casting:**
* **Jerry Seatman**

**Ethnicity**: White / European Descent 

**Rate:** $400/Day, (est. 2 days of work)

**Role Description:**

Male, 43–55, A middle-aged man who also happens to be a literal human-car-seat hybrid. 

Mostly facial acting, we are looking for someone to portray a middle-aged, defeated, working family man then having his major transformation. Think used car salesman, or insurance salesman. 

Notes: Actors should be comfortable with light physical comedy and playing sincerity within an absurd premise. Prosthetics / costume elements may be involved to emulate the human-car-seat look.

* **Nancy**

**Ethnicity**: White / European Descent 

**Rate:** $400/Day, (est. 1 day of work)

**Role Description:**

Female, 36-46, Warm, observant, and quietly supportive. She sees Jerry’s insecurities before he says them out loud and ultimately gives him the gift that changes everything. This role requires emotional subtlety and natural warmth.

* **Daughter**

**Ethnicity**: White / European Descent 

**Rate:** $300/Day, (est. 1 day of work)

**Role Description:**

Female, 9-14, Bright, affectionate, and playful. Natural, expressive, comfortable on camera.

* **Son**

**Ethnicity**: White / European Descent 

**Rate:** $300/Day, (est. 1 day of work)

**Role Description:**

Male, 9-14, Energetic and joyful. Looking for natural, playful energy.

Evgeni, a non-speaking little boy living in Russia is told his abusive father is going to be killed. Despite having a chance to save him, he lets his father die to end his torment. 19 years later, Evgeni is put in a position to save another man’s life, though it will cost him his freedom. 

***see casting call poster for more info about characters***

Director: Matey Enchevich

Volunteer Position
Lunch, Snack and drinks provided 

Special note: 
‼️ Actors don’t have to be fluent in ASL but must at least know ASL and are willing to learn 

Send headshots by December 30th 2025 to albatross.filmprod@gmail.com

items.text:
Hello,

My name is Allison and I am the producer for the Student Short Film** “Soundly Awake”** at VFS Film Production Program. We are currently looking for Non-Union Actors to cast in our film!

**Project Title:** Soundly Awake

**Project Type:** Student Short Film

**Union Status: **Non-Union

**Director:** Raj Heer

**Producer:** Allison Wall

**Casting Director:** Allison Wall

**Audition Dates:** Self-tapes due by January 8th, 2026

**Audition Location:** Self-tapes only

**Call Back Dates:** January 11th, 2026

**Call Back Location:** 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2

**Shooting Dates: **January 27th - January 29th  

**Shooting Location:** Greater Vancouver Area

**Rates:** Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.

**Submission Instructions:**

Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel (if applicable) to soundlyawakefilm@gmail.com and indicate which role you’d like to be considered for.

**Synopsis:**

Haunted by recurring nightmares of his abusive father, Jun, a lonely and withdrawn man, meets Sage, a curious nightmare eater who appears to “consume” his pain. As Sage helps ease Jun’s suffering in the Between, Jun begins to open his heart, finding the strength to confront his father in the real world. When the nightmares end and Sage has to leave, Jun is heartbroken, fearing he will never see Sage again, until an unexpected reunion proves that some bonds endure beyond dreams.

Chris xx

12/12/25

(This Is My) Family (Short Film)

A Comedy about family dynamics

A family near breaking point, implodes in one night. 

Shooting April location TBC

Auditioning: We want to receive self tapes first and those who make it to the next stage, we would love in person auditions by late January of 2026. 

Travel Expenses paid

Student film being screened at The BFI and will be entered into film festivals

Elizabeth (50s-60s) - Narcissistic mother who dominates her kids' lives. She speaks her mind much to the reluctance of everyone around her..

Marie (30s-40s) - She’s in the middle of a mid-life crisis and she blames elizabeth as she thinks she’s not the perfect mother that she presents herself as. So Marie rebels against this supposed ‘perfect family’.

Shaun (30-40s) - Shaun simply accepts his place in the world and has very little self respect. He is in a loveless relationship with his wife (Claire) however he does not rebel against her out of fear of living life alone in his 40s. Yet again every man has his breaking point. 

Clare (30s-40s) - Clare needs power and control, so she has found a man she can excerpt this power on (Shaun.) Clare and Elizabeth are very similar and therefore team up to inflate each other's egos at the expense of Marie and Shaun. 

Email: tylerbrownework@gmail.com for further details

Please only respond if you are based in England as our budget will not cover travel from abroad.

items.text:
We are casting confident, expressive individuals to appear as contestants/guests on a high-energy, unscripted talk show inspired by classic formats such as Jeremy Kyle and Jerry Springer.

The show will be hosted by massive influencer, who will take the role of the presenter, guiding conversations, mediating disputes, and attempting to resolve real or semi-scripted personal conflicts in an entertaining, fast-paced environment.

This is a performance-based role requiring strong personality, emotional range, and the ability to react naturally on camera.

Role Description – Contestants / Guests

Selected participants will appear on the show as individuals involved in a personal conflict, relationship issue, family dispute, secret reveal, or moral dilemma. Scenarios may include (but are not limited to):

Relationship breakdowns or accusations

Love triangles or cheating allegations

Friendship or family fallouts

Hidden secrets or confrontations

Lifestyle or behavioural conflicts

You will be expected to:

Play a character or heightened version of yourself

Engage in open, confrontational, or emotionally charged discussions

React naturally to questions, accusations, and audience/chat interaction

Remain in character throughout the segment

Be comfortable with raised voices, dramatic moments, and comedic tension

Ideal Candidate

Aged 18+

Confident and expressive on camera

Comfortable with confrontation and emotional performance

Strong improvisation skills (acting experience is a plus, but not required)

Able to think quickly and respond naturally in live situations

Thick-skinned and comfortable being part of viral, high-reach content

Important Notes

This is entertainment content, not a real counselling or therapy show

Scenarios may be planned, semi-scripted, or improvised

Content will be broadcast live and clipped for social platforms (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, etc.)

Applicants must consent to being filmed and distributed online

Compensation

Paid role

Rate dependent on role complexity, screen time, and experience

topComments.text: Looking for uneducated thickos with anger problems. Got it.
People who wash their dirty linen in public for cash .  Have we not grown out of these shows .

**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk )**

 

Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć. Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 35 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania, na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw do kobieta: Piękna i drapieżna! Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

** **

**Zapraszam na stronę**

** **

**Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

www.instagram.com/lukasz.magiera.official

Więcej informacji na Priv

**HORT FILM CASTING CALL – INDIGENOUS FEMALE ACTOR**

**Project Type:** Independent Short Film
**Location:** Vancouver, BC
**Shoot Dates:** March, 2026
**ROLE**
* **Indigenous / First Nations / Métis / Inuit female actor**
* **Age range:** approx. 18–25
* Acting experience preferred but not required
**CHARACTER**
* A quiet, observant young woman navigating a moment of personal change.
**REQUIREMENTS**
* Must self-identify as Indigenous
* Based in Vancouver or able to work locally
* Comfortable working on an independent short film set
**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)
* (Optional) Demo reel or self-tape

**Submit to:** hiayj23@gmail.com

items.text:
**Hej!** Jesteśmy Centrum Polonijne – szkoła języka polskiego. Poszukujemy osób pełnych energii i pasji do edukacji, które potrafią nie tylko grać, lecz także wspaniale opowiadać.

🎯 **Cel:** Tworzenie krótkich edukacyjno-poznawczych filmików na YouTube oraz Instagram (SMM).

🇵🇱 Celem tych materiałów będzie edukowanie naszych uczniów na temat Polski, jej kultury, życia codziennego oraz memów!

👉 Przykładowo: https://www.instagram.com/centrum_polonijne/

🧑‍🎤 **Kogo szukamy:**
* 🌟 Młode osoby (18–35 lat) z dobrą wymową i znajomością rosyjskiego na poziomie co najmniej B1 **lub **rosyjskojęzyczne osoby ze znajomością polskiego na poziomie co najmniej C1.
* 📹 Umiejętność nagrywania filmów i montażu jest konieczna. 
* 🎓 Doświadczenie przed kamerą lub w nauczaniu to dodatkowy atut.
* 😊 Ktoś, kto ma miłą aparycję i potrafi przyciągnąć uwagę widzów.

✉️ **Jak do nas dołączyć:**

Prześlij CV oraz krótkie wideo (nagrane telefonem) z prezentacją na adres: **info@polonijne.pl**

🚀 **Czekamy na Ciebie!** Razem twórzmy niesamowity content edukacyjny!

items.text:
🎬 CASTING CALL – STUDENT SHORT FILM 🎬

**UNPAID**

Hey everyone! I’m currently casting for my upcoming short film, *After the Rain*, an intimate emotional drama about two sisters navigating the aftermath of their mother’s sudden death. When a violent storm forces Mia and Isla back together, unspoken grief and buried pain rise to the surface, pushing them toward understanding, healing, and renewed connection.

To be shot in: High Wycombe/ London 

**Synopsis:**

After their mother’s sudden death, two sisters are pulled apart by grief, distance, and unspoken pain. Mia, the older sister, leaves to pursue a promising job opportunity, trying to outrun the heartbreak of their loss. Isla stays behind, sinking into isolation and self-destructive behaviour as her distress deepens. When Mia returns on a stormy night to find Isla drunk and unravelling, the sisters are forced to confront years of buried resentment and abandonment. Through raw confessions and shared vulnerability, they begin a journey towards understanding, forgiveness, and the possibility of hope, finding solace in the quiet strength of sisterhood. 

Characters:

**ISLA (19-22, FEMALE)** 

impulsive, reckless, emotionally unstable little sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and intoxication.  

**MIA (25-28, FEMALE)**

protective, compassionate, responsible older sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and the effects of grief. 

Shooting: DATES TBC  (approx JAN 6-16th)    

If interested, please contact me for more information at austenfilmworks@gmail.com 

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested. 🎥🎬

items.text:
🎬 CASTING CALL – STUDENT FINAL FILM 🎬

**PAID** Hi everyone! We are currently casting for WISP, a haunting coming-of-age drama about isolation, queer longing, and the grip of an unseen presence.

To be Shot in: West Yorkshire.

 

Synopsis:

Sixteen-year-old Noah has spent weeks drifting from everyone he loves,

manipulated by an unseen presence. When his best friend Sam turns up on New Year’s Eve, Noah finds himself caught between feelings he’s long buried and the Voice that refuses to let him go.

 

Characters:

NOAH (16–25, male) – Quiet, introspective, emotionally guarded. Must be able to convey internal conflict, subtle fear, and vulnerability with restraint.

SAM (16–25, male) – Warm, intuitive, and grounded. Noah’s best friend; emotionally open, present, and deeply human.

 

Shooting: 12/2 – 15/2   (Night Shoots)

Payment: TBD — we are happy to discuss this with you.          

 

📩 Contact: [jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com](mailto:jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com) with Showreel if available. Script will be available.

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested.  🌳🖤

sharedPost.text:
Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 51/2025

ENDLICH STARTET DER MEGA BLOCKBUSTER UND FILME FÜR DIE JÜNGSTEN

Nach 3jähriger Pause lässt uns James Cameron mit AVATAR: FIRE AND ASH erneut in die Welt von Pandora eintauchen. Ob der Film wahrlich ein Meisterwerk ist, erfahren Sie in unserer Sendung.

Weihnachtszeit ist jene Zeit in der das jüngste Publikum voll auf ihre Rechnung kommt, sei es in den Lichtspielen Gföhl oder im Kronenkino Mistelbach und so ganz nebenbei startet das neueste SpongeBob Abenteuer. 

Mitte Februar dieses Jahres wurde das Kino Horn neu übernommen und nennt sich seitdem Babylon Kino. Warum gerade dieser Name gewählt wurde bzw. was alles zum Alltag eines Kinobetriebes gehört, erzählt uns Ralph Guczky.

Weitere Filmtipps und die beliebtesten Movie Christmas Hits,  präsentiert Ihnen Filmexpertin, Sarah Fuchs. 

Mittwoch 17.12.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

## **CASTING CALL – “TETRACHROMACY” (Short Film)**

**Project Title:** *Tetrachromacy*

**Genre:** Drama

**Location:** Vancouver, BC

**Shoot Dates:** December 29 & 30, 2025

**Compensation:** Indie film, great experience, Volunteer project (we are all volunteers, there’s no budget.)

Synopsis

*Tetrachromacy* follows **Nathan**, a photojournalist who loses his ability to see color after a head injury, leaving his world in stark black and white. One year later, he discovers that color returns only through AI-recreated images of his photographs. His life shifts when he encounters **Claire**, a woman in a yellow dress who appears vividly in color within his monochromatic reality, challenging his isolation and reshaping his sense of connection.

Role breakdown
NATHAN(Lead, 30s, male)

* A passionate photojournalist with a strong artistic eye
* Suffers from cerebral achromatopsia following a head injury
* Intelligent, introspective, emotionally reserved
* Slightly awkward when expressing feelings
* **Emotional arc:** moves from isolation and frustration toward wonder, openness, and human connection

**Notes:**

This is a subtle, performance-driven role. Actor must be comfortable conveying emotion through restraint, stillness, and internal conflict.

Submission Details

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (or relevant acting experience)
* Demo reel (if available)
* A short Self-tape

**Submit to:** [s6films.co@gmail.com](mailto:s6films.co@gmail.com)

**Submission Deadline:** December 21, 2025

If selected auditions will be hosted on December 22, 2025

Who we are:

S6 films is a a group of passionate filmmakers pursuing creating films we care about amidst busy life and jobs in video production.

Looking for **ONE MALE ACTOR (Age 45–65)** for a lead role in a short psychological film.

**Role:**
A disturbed, emotionally fragile middle-aged man. No dialogue. Performance relies heavily on facial expression, physicality, and emotional presence.

**Shoot Details:**
– Student film project
– 1 Shoot day
– Location: Vancouver
– Shooting date: TBD

**Requirements:**
– Comfortable portraying intense emotional states
– Must be expressive on camera
– No previous experience required

**To Apply:**
Please send a headshot (or recent photo), age, and a brief note about your acting experience to:

borovinskiymax@gmail.com

Serious inquiries only

**Szukam modelki XL na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk )**

** **

**‘’Rubensowskie kształty’’**

 

Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć. Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator. Motyw główny to nawiązanie do xvi wiecznego malarza Paula Rubensa.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 20 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania, na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

** **

**Zapraszam na stronę**

** **

**Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

www.instagram.com/lukasz.magiera.official

Więcej informacji na Priv

sharedPost.text:
Mając zasadniczo pod sobą dość dużą ilość grupowiczów, czy też grupowiczek, regulamin FB jest w jakiś tam sposób jednak wsparciem. Takim samym wsparciem jest także podejście rodziców do dziecka, ale i jedno, i drugie można czasem ominąć.

Jak już wspominałem przy okazji postu „Twoja córka”, tak wspomnę także i teraz, że należałoby rozmawiać ze swoimi dzieciaszkami. Ewidentnie niektórzy rodzice tego nie robią, bo tak jak dajecie swoim stworkom komórki, to i trudno wymagać od osoby w takim wieku wyjątkowej dojrzałości życiowej. FB zezwala na założenie konta osobom od 13 lat w górę, ale jak widać nie zawsze jest to respektowane przez same zainteresowane.

Wcześniej starałem się sam rozmawiać, ale niestety bardzo często nie miałem jak do nich dotrzeć. Albo dosłownie mnie blokowano, albo pomimo wyrażenia woli podjęcia kontaktu ze strony zewnętrznej, nawiązanie rozmowy było nierealne, gdyż FB to blokował. Po prostu starając się dotrzeć do takich osób musiałem założyć, że same otrzymały pozwolenie ze strony rodziców, a i tak zapewne w ogromnej części przypadków sami rodzice o tym i z pewnością nie wiedzieli.

FB daje też możliwość zgłaszania kont osób, które nie mają 13 lat, ale takowe zgłoszenia nigdy w moim przynajmniej przypadku nie zostały rozpatrzone. Dość dużą ciekawostką są także i grupy, które są przeznaczone dla osób dosłownie małoletnich, gdzie mogą one znaleźć dla siebie pracę, a przypomnę tylko, że takową w Polsce wg prawa można świadczyć od 15 roku życia w górę.

Dlatego też Drodzy Państwo, rodzice i Wy dzieciątka, od dzisiaj w górę takowe osoby będą blokowane po stwierdzeniu, że macie do 13 lat. Wcześniej starałem się jakoś do Was dotrzeć, że nie mogę wiecznie liczyć, że przekazywanie informacji przez Was będzie stałe, czy też, że w ogóle będzie miało miejsce? Agentura ma swoje prawa, ale to w tej części trzeba zmienić.

items.text:
Cześć!

Poszukujemy aktorów do kampanii reklamowej samochodów 🚗

Termin zdjęć: 8/01/2026 i 10/01/2026, Warszawa i okolice

**Młody ojciec (Mężczyzna, ok. 37 lat):** 

Typ: "Modern Dad". To nie jest zagubiony rodzic, ale facet, który ogarnia chaos z uśmiechem.
Wygląd: Zadbany, ale na luzie. Casualowy styl - jeansy, T- shirt, może fajna kurtka. Wygląda na kogoś, kto potrafi naprawić zabawkę i jednocześnie świetnie prowadzić auto. 

**Kobieta (Kobieta, ok. 30 lat):**

Typ: "Smart Professional". Menadżerka, która właśnie dopięła projekt i z satysfakcją zamyka laptopa.
Wygląd: Naturalnie atrakcyjna, "smart casual". Wygląda profesjonalnie, ale nie sztywno. Widać, że dba o siebie, ale jej uroda jest przystępna.

**Ogrodnik (Mężczyzna, ok. 50 lat):**

Typ: "The Woodsman". Facet zżyty z naturą, dla którego ogród to drugi dom. Pracuje ciężko fizycznie, ale jest doświadczonym fachowcem.
Wygląd: Twarz z charakterem, "z historią", ogorzała od wiatru i słońca. Może mieć gęstszy zarost. Jest silny, krzepki, budzi respekt i zaufanie.

**Informacje o stawkach i zakresie praw prześlę w wiadomości prywatnej.**

**Każda osoba biorąca udział w castingu musi posiadać czynne prawo jazdy kategorii B oraz na codzień jeździć samochodem!**

**Osoby zainteresowane udziałem prosimy o przesłanie:**

**- selftape z wizytówką (prosimy o linki do Youtube)**

**- 2 zdjęcia - portretowe oraz całej sylwetki (nie przyjmujemy linków do social mediów, zdjęcia muszą być dołączone jako załącznik wiadomości)**

**Zgłoszenia proszę nadsyłać do 20/12/2026 (sobota) do godziny 18:00 na adres: bioreudzialwcastingu@gmail.com 📩**

# ‼️Casting Call! 

Wir suchen einen Darsteller oder eine Darstellerin im Alter von ca. 40–50 Jahren für einen Image- und How-to-Dreh im handwerklichen Bereich. 

**Anforderungen:**

– authentisches Auftreten

– handwerkliches Geschick (bitte keine zwei linken Hände)

– Freude am Thema DIY/Handwerk

– kleine Sprechrolle vor der Kamera

– Drehtag in NRW, voraussichtlich im Januar/Februar.

Gage ist verhandelbar und wird vom Darsteller selber festgelegt!

Option auf regelmäßige Folgeprojekte. 🤩

[https://go.castfinder.de/darsteller-fr-imagefilm-gesucht/](https://go.castfinder.de/darsteller-fr-imagefilm-gesucht/)

items.text:
Dieses Erklärvideo (KI generiert) ist ein Auszug, vielleicht eher eine verkürzte Zusammenfassung, des Buches "HAGIA SOFIA, Siehst Du noch den Weißen Turm", und enthält sowohl narrative Kapitel als auch umfangreiche Quellenangaben und formale Abschnitte. Die fiktive Haupthandlung dreht sich um eine Gruppe von Protagonisten, darunter die Historiker 

Elias und Nikos sowie Geheimdienstagenten, die versuchen, einen 

verheerenden Terroranschlag des sogenannten "Schattenkonvents" auf die Hagia Sofia in Thessaloniki zu verhindern, wobei die "Sonne von Vergina" als Code-Botschaft dient. Parallel zur Thriller-Erzählung über Verfolgungsjagden und das Entschlüsseln von Hinweisen im Weißen Turm und in Katakomben werden detaillierte geopolitische und strategische Hintergründe

 präsentiert, die Thessalonikis Rolle als zentraler Verkehrsknotenpunkt 

und Energie-Hub sowie die tief verwurzelten Spannungen zwischen 

Griechenland, der Türkei und anderen regionalen Akteuren hervorheben. 

Die umfangreichen Quellenverweise belegen die historischen, geografischen und militärischen Fakten, die als Basis für die fiktive Geschichte über False Flag Operationen und die Destabilisierung der Region dienen.

FREE Photoshoot & Workshop

Important: You must attend both the photoshoot and the workshop in Week 5.
Limited spots. Apply now in the Selfcast app: https://selfcast.com/for-talents/

See you on Selfcast

@selfcastapp @selfcast.tr @mariachristinaselfcast @philipdessau @arinuriye16

sharedPost.text:
AUDITONS FOR RAG DOLLY - THE RAGGEDY ANN MUSICAL WORKSHOP 

Seeking actors for a public workshop reading of Rag Dolly. In Rag Dolly, a little girl named Marcella is dying of a mysterious illness. Her father makes her a rag doll to comfort her, and his stories of the doll come to life in her dreams to guide her through her grief and fear. Marcella and her new friends confront wolves, witches, and incompetent doctors on their way to outwit death and mend her broken heart.

https://forms.gle/zgcr7fphzWhbmNjRA

items.text:
**PAID OPPORTUNITY – Origin Originals**

📢 Calling all women with extraordinary true stories!

We’re launching a brand-new series for Origin (650k+), the platform where **women share their most intimate, powerful, and unforgettable real-life experiences.**

We're looking for women with extraordinary true stories: parenting, disability, sexuality, addiction, and beyond. If your story is shocking, unforgettable, or something people won't believe, we want to share it.

If that sounds like you (or someone you know), get in touch!

🇬🇧 You must be based in the UK to apply.

🎥 This is a** paid opportunity** and filming happens in a** London** studio.

📧 Send your video tape submission to: **[mireille.lee@upstream-media.co.uk](mailto:mireille.lee@upstream-media.co.uk)**

https://www.youtube.com/@_origin

message.text:
David Reynolds returns for one reason.
To jump.

Years of military PTSD and childhood trauma have followed him home.
His battles are no longer fought outside.
They live in his head.
And no matter where he runs, there is no escape.

The bridge stands waiting.
Cold. Hard. Steel.
Resilient, yet weakened every time someone walks across it.
A mirror of the man standing before it.

David comes back broken.
Ready to end it.

Then he learns the truth.
He has a son.

For a moment, hope breaks through.

It does not last.

Grief and fury collide.
David turns outward, cleaning up the mess around him.
But his greatest enemy was never out there.

It was always himself.

David Reynolds.
And he will not go gentle.

This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

items.summary:
This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

items.text:
Genre: Dark fantasy / Psychological Horror

Length: 25 - 30 minutes

Location: BERLIN 

Shooting: End of January/ Beginning of February

Budget: unpaid (graduation film)

Hey everyone, we are casting several supporting roles for a dark atmospheric graduation proof-of-concept film that blends mythology, psychological horror, and realism. This project explores power, identity, and the uncanny hidden beneath everyday life.

If you’re a fan of The Sandman, Pan’s Labrynth, and Only Lovers Left Alive, then you will feel right at home.

Actors of all backgrounds are encouraged to apply.

ROLES AVAILABLE

Spati owner (30s - 60s) - Male

A grounded ordinary presence in the mortal world. Calm and slightly detached. The Spati owner acts as an anchor to reality before things begin to unravel.

Ria (20s - 30s) - Female

Sharp, perceptive, emotionally guarded. She carries tension beneath casual conversation.

Pierre (20s - 30s) - Male

Charming on the surface but unsettling underneath. He speaks easily but holds something back.

Darius (20s - 30s) - Male

Charismatic, confident, slightly arrogant. Darius is a natural leader in social spaces. However, under pressure, his warmth slips.

Coveliat (30s) - Female

A creature of death. Uncanny, ritualistic presence, more felt than understood. Her claws can slash through the strongest of materials.

Girl 1 (20s) - Female

Social, warm, slightly obvious. She represents normality and comfort, until that comfort curdles into unease.

Girl 2 (20s -30s) - Female

More observant than girl 1. She picks up on subtle shifts in tone and energy. Friendly, but with flickers of suspicion.

IF INTERESTED

We would kindly ask you to send an email to:

celia.t@catalyst-students.com

The submission will be done in the form of self-tapes rather than in-person auditions.

The self-tape information will be sent via email.

Looking forward to hearing from you!

items.text: Come audit this weekly class that takes place right here in Sandy on Monday, Tuesday, or Wednesday nights and take your ability to the next level. Every student performs in front of the class every week. What decides auditions is the quality of the audition tape and what determines the quality of your tape is your Understanding of BEATS and ACTIONS and equally important - YOUR ABILITY TO EMOTIONALLY BRING THE GOODS with simplicity and precision. Come sit in on a class to see what it's all about.

items.text:
The Cottage
By Sandy Rustin
Directed by Ben Green
Auditions:
Monday, January 5, and Tuesday, January 6 at @ 7:00pm
Callback by invitation on Wednesday January 7 @ 7pm

Play Overview:
A fast-paced, heightened comedic farce set in 1923 England. Infidelity, mistaken identities, exaggerated manners, and bold physical comedy drive the show. All roles require strong comedic timing, physicality, and the ability to deliver heightened, crisp dialogue in a British dialect.

The director encourages diverse casting. No role has a strict requirement of ethnicity or race.

Physicality & Intimacy: Farcical timing, comedic blocking, and in some roles intimacy scenes (kissing / romantic chemistry) are required; also comedic violence or slapstick may appear.

As the play is set in 1923 England: RP / British accent is required.

Character Breakdown:
Sylvia
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s
Description: A “lovely and rash romantic.” Sylvia is impulsive, passionate, and clings to romantic idealism. She’s the one who initiates the comedic uproar by deciding to reveal her affair which triggers the farcical unraveling of secrets.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should embody flirtatious charm, emotional volatility, and physical energy. Expect moments of passion/intimacy (kissing or romantic touch) and heightened comedic reactions or slapstick. 

Beau
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Beau is described as “perhaps the best-looking man in Britain.” He’s charming, handsome, and somewhat complacent. A man comfortable with the status quo, even when his romantic life is scandalous. His affair with Sylvia is marked by both desire and hesitation.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should have presence, charm, and ease. Needs comfort with intimacy (romantic scenes) and comedic timing, especially with farcical elements. RP British accent.

Marjorie
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s (she is very pregnant in the play)
Description: Beau’s wife. “Eight months pregnant, pragmatic”, grounded, and composed, even in the face of shocking revelations. Underneath, she has a sharp edge; she’s “a tad spicy.” 
Physical / Performance Notes: You will be wearing an insanely pregnant-belly. Needs emotional range: from shock to self preservation to possible betrayal or strength. Comedic instincts + ability to react strongly to chaos.

Clarke
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Sylvia’s husband. A refined, “distinguished gent with a lover’s spirit.” He may appear respectable and stable, but underneath, his loyalties and feelings are complicated. Entangled in the web of affairs and deceptions.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs a balance of dignity and vulnerability. Believable as a gentleman, but also capable of comedic panic or confusion. Comfortable with farce pacing and quick reaction work. 

Dierdre
Gender: Female
Age: Early 20s to 30s (or thereabouts, though exact age is flexible)
Description: She’s described in the script as “an awfully pretty, sometimes wise, nincompoop.” She’s naïve, sweet, perhaps a bit ditzy, but also occasionally offers piercing insight. She often reacts to the chaos with bewilderment and innocence, which amplifies the comedy.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs to deliver endearing innocence, comedic timing, and willingness to play “ditzy” with heart. Should be comfortable with exaggerated reactions, physical comedy and the heightened energy of farce. 

Richard
Gender: Male
Age: 30s to 50s
Description: A dark comedic twist in the farce. Richard is described as “murderous” but “gentle,” meaning he occupies the role of destabilizing danger amidst the comedic chaos. His arrival triggers tension, threat, and unexpected comedy. A perfect blend of menace and absurdity.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should be able to handle heightened dramatic tension and farcical comedy. Perhaps a little brooding, but also capable of shambling comedy or over-the-top melodrama. Must be okay with comedic threat, possibly physical acting (gun or
threat).

Bring a headshot and resume and be ready to list ALL conflicts.

Performances: February 27 to March 22, 2026
Rehearsals Begin January 12 at Cabrillo Playhouse
All genders, body types, and ethnicities are encouraged to audition
There is a small stipend offered

STUDENT SHORT FILM CASTING 

Shooting dates: 23rd-25th January

Location: Vancouver, North Vancouver

Volunteer, lunch and copy of film provided. 

**MARTY (20-25)**
* A young pianist struggling with anxiety and health issues. His passion for music is strong, but he is haunted by self-doubt and physical limitations. Emotionally vulnerable, he carries the weight of the past, yet despite the toll on his body and mind, he persists in pursuing his dreams.

**MARTY'S MOTHER (40s-50s)**
* A supportive, hard-working single mother. Cares deeply for her son and masks her worries about his skill with a calm, composed demeanor, despite the mental and physical toll it’s taking on her.

**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to an audition, January 7th. If unavailable, a self-tape will be accepted. 

**Submit to:** melodymovie2026@gmail.com

**NOW CASTING – LA Based Gen Z Contestants for a Series of New Digital Game Shows!**

A major cable company’s digital channel is looking for Gen Z contestants for game shows in Los Angeles!

Contestants should be outgoing, competitive and looking to have fun. We are producing a series of different shows that will be centered around Gen Z trivia, physical competitions and dating – so there is a show for everyone!

In your submission, please let us know if you are single and want to be on a dating game show. We are open to all genders and sexual orientations.

Also, let us know if you are a pro when it comes to sports or Bible trivia.

**Apply today by emailing**  d3gameshowcasting@gmail.com with the following information:

Name · Phone Number · Email Address · Current Location · Recent Photos · Social Media Handles 

Filming will take place January 2026 in Los Angeles, CA. All applicants must be at least 18 years old, live in the LA area and be US Citizens or permanent residents of the United States.

items.text:
I recently had a detailed conversation with Kurt Evans of Artist2Artist, one of the established actor showcase platforms, specifically around demo reels, self-tapes, and how casting actually encounters actors.

A few points from that discussion are worth sharing, because they clarify a lot of confusion I keep seeing among actors at different stages.

On demo reels:
Casting directors are not ignoring traditional demo reels. A professional demo reel is still exactly that — the professional work you’ve done, compiled into a roughly three-minute video. What matters is how that reel is structured.

Rather than one or two long scenes, the reel works best when it’s made up of multiple 20–30 second sections, each clearly showing a type you would naturally be called in for — parent, authority figure, professional roles, etc. The goal isn’t to replace the reel, but to make it immediately readable. Realistically, a director may only watch about 20 seconds before deciding whether you fit, so clarity matters more than length.

On highly produced self-tapes:
We spoke about the rise of very cinematic, highly produced self-tapes — essentially mini-movies. Kurt isn’t against production value. In fact, he shared an example where one panelist loved a highly edited tape, while another felt it looked more like a finished production than an audition.

The key point he emphasized is that the purpose of a self-tape or showcase submission is still to evaluate acting. Most actors audition two to three times a week. It’s neither realistic nor necessary to shoot a short film every time. What casting needs is a clear window into the performance. Overproduction isn’t a mistake — it’s just not what casting is primarily judging.

On agents and casting access:
This is the part many actors misunderstand. Casting primarily encounters actors through agents. It’s not about gatekeeping or access — it’s how the system functions. There’s a trust relationship between agents and casting offices.

In a traditional setting, a casting assistant may block off hours of time, receive hundreds of short submissions from agents, and narrow those down to about twenty strong fits. That’s how casting begins to connect with talent. Without representation, casting offices often have no way of knowing an actor exists.

What showcases like Artist2Artist aim to do is create a space where casting can watch actors work outside the volume and time pressure of the standard submission pipeline.

The takeaway from the conversation was straightforward:
For actors who want to be seen consistently in film and television, representation is the first gateway into that ecosystem.

Pay is from £50-£250 per hour, events include meet and greets, parties, love shows and video calls for clients across the UK, but most bookings will be London and surrounding areas.
